                                <span id="ContentPlaceHolder1_JobDetails2_lblDescription" class="jobDetail_jobDesc_Content"><p>Leadership opportunity here!! Our team is responsible for protecting data in transit and at rest for the next generation of operating systems. Our team provides the core crypto components for the operating system and is responsible for end to end scenarios like BitLocker, Device Encryption and Windows Information Protection.<br></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>We are looking to apply data driven analysis to improve our future offerings to our consumers. If you love project and people management in addition to being fascinated by Security and are passionate about quality, look no further.<br></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>If you are excited to grow a team of engineers to learn how to process and visualize patterns in data - all with the end goal of shipping great customer scenarios with excellent quality - I need you!<br></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Basic Requirements:<br></p>
<p> <br></p>
<p>•7+ years managing teams and projects<br></p>
<p>•7+ years of experience in software engineering<br></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Preferred Qualifications:<br></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>•Solid C#/C++ coding, design and debugging skills<br></p>
<p>•Solid spoken and written communication skills<br></p>
<p>•Ability to deal with ambiguity<br></p>
<p>•Great problem solving skills and high intellectual horsepower<br></p>
<p>•Experience shipping multiple complete ship cycles<br></p>
<p>•Great leadership skills; excellent collaboration skills; great project management skills<br></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Desired (not required):<br></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>-Experience in data sciences &amp; analytics, Solid SQL and Data Analysis skills<br></p>
<p>-Experience with Cryptography, Trust Management, TPM, Data protection, Rights Management is a plus<br></p>
<p>-Product engineering experience working on OS components, security, data protection<br></p>
<p>-BA/BS or advanced degree in Computer Science or Electrical Engineering preferred<br></p>
<p><br></p>
<p>Microsoft is an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, religion, national origin or ancestry, age, disability, marital status, pregnancy, protected veteran status, protected genetic information, political affiliation, or any other characteristics protected by local laws, regulations, or ordinances.</p>
